bayou.jtype

Class JavaType<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • bayou.jtype.JavaType<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PrimitiveType, ReferenceType

    public abstract class JavaType<T>
extends Object
    Any Java type.

    The hierarchy of types: 

         JavaType
         PrimitiveType
         ReferenceType
             ClassType
             ArrayType
             TypeVar
             IntersectionType
             NullType

    Example usage: 

         JavaType<String> typeString = ClassType.of(String.class);

    • Method Detail

      • toString

        public abstract String toString(boolean full)
        A textual description of the type.

        If `full==false`, simpler names are used for types.

        For example: 

            ClassType< List<String> > type = ClassType.of(List.class, String.class);

    type.toString(true);    //  "java.util.List<java.lang.String>"
    type.toString(false);   //  "List<String>"

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object obj)
        Whether this type is equal to another type.

        Equality is only tested syntactically. It is possible that type A,B are equivalent, e.g. `A<:B and B<:A`, yet `A.equals(B)==false`.

        To check equivalency through mutual subtyping, use TypeMath.isSubType.

        Overrides:
        equals in class Object

      • convertFrom

        public static <T> JavaType<T> convertFrom(Type jlrType)
        Convert a java.lang.reflect.Type to bayou.jtype.JavaType

        This method does not accept java.lang.reflect.WildcardType, because a wildcard is not a type.
